						               													<description>Flipcards is the perfect gamer gift, it's a beautifully illustrated postcard you can send to a friend or beloved one, but it is also a game that you can play with one to one hundred friends, just toss the postcard on the table, when it stops the game begins: any player can BID (i.e. declare) the number of FLIPS they think the postcard needs to do to REACH THE EDGE of the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To make ONE FLIP means to flip the postcard from one face to the other, HINGING on any one of its SIDES.&amp;#10;The other players can pass or make further LOWER bids.&amp;#10;When all players but one have passed, the WINNING BIDDER has to FLIP the postcard AS MANY TIMES OR LESS as their BID to reach the border of the table, if they succeed to do so they win the round; cut along the dotted line and give the piece cut to the winning bidder. Otherwise, the ROUND IS LOST, and the bidder has to CRUMPLE the piece of the postcard just received. Players with two crumpled pieces in front of them are ELIMINATED. After a piece has been cut from the postcard, start a new round.&amp;#10;The game GOES ON until the final piece has been cut from the postcard or all players but one have been ELIMINATED. The non-eliminated player with the most victory point on their non-crumpled pieces is the winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
